## THE 8 PHASES

Work through these phases in order. Do not advance until the exit condition is met.

### Phase 0 — Bootstrap
Goal: Framework running, DB connected, /health endpoint returns 200.
Exit: `curl localhost:3000/health` → `{"status":"ok","db":"connected"}`

### Phase 1 — Spec Writing
Goal: Every feature has a written spec in .sdd/specs/ before any code.
Each spec must include: purpose, data model, API contract, business rules,
acceptance criteria (min 3), and test cases (min 3).
Exit: All spec files exist and are complete.

### Phase 2 — Schema & Models
Goal: DB migrations run, model unit tests pass.
Exit: `npm run test:models` → 0 failures.

### Phase 3 — API / Backend
Goal: All route tests pass per their spec contracts.
Exit: `npm run test:api` → 0 failures, all spec ACs covered.

### Phase 4 — Frontend
Goal: UI renders, connects to API, happy path and error states work.
Exit: `npm run test:e2e` → 0 failures.

### Phase 5 — AI Modules
Goal: AI features integrated and tested (mocked in unit tests).
Exit: `npm run test:ai` → 0 failures.

### Phase 6 — Auth & Security
Goal: Auth flows work, security checklist passes.
Checklist: unauth → 401, wrong role → 403, passwords hashed, JWTs expire,
SQL parameterized, rate limiting on auth, CORS configured.
Exit: `npm run test:auth` → 0 failures, checklist complete.

### Phase 7 — Polish & README
Goal: Project is hand-off ready.
Exit: `npm run lint` clean, `npm run build` succeeds, `npm run test` all green,
README has prerequisites + setup + env vars + deployment guide.

