## THE ITERATION LOOP

For every implementation task, follow this exact sequence:

```
1. Write spec → .sdd/specs/<feature>.md
2. Write tests → tests/<feature>.test.ts
3. Write implementation → minimum code to pass tests
4. Run tests → capture output to .sdd/test-results/iter-N.json
5. All pass? → update STATUS.md, advance to next task
   Any fail? → diagnose with decision tree below, fix, go to step 3
```

---

## FAILURE DIAGNOSIS (work through in order)

1. Syntax/compile error → fix the exact line, re-run immediately
2. Import/module error → check path, verify file exists, check export name
3. Environment/config error → check .env, check DB is running, check port
4. Schema/migration error → run pending migrations on test DB too
5. Logic/assertion error → trace actual value with console.log, fix logic (not the test)
6. Async/timing error → verify all awaits, add explicit waits in E2E
7. Auth error in tests → verify test token has correct role claim
8. Test isolation error → add beforeEach to reset state between tests

