## TECH STACK (Next.js + MySQL + React + AI)

### Structure
- API routes: src/app/api/ (route handlers only, no business logic)
- Services: src/lib/services/ (business logic)
- Repositories: src/lib/db/repositories/ (all SQL here, nowhere else)
- Validations: src/lib/validations/ (Zod schemas)
- AI modules: src/lib/ai/ (wrapped, always with fallback)

### DB
- Use mysql2/promise with connection pool
- Migrations in src/lib/db/migrations/ numbered sequentially
- Always parameterized queries — never string interpolation
- Separate test DB configured via DB_NAME_TEST env var

### Auth
- NextAuth.js v5 (Auth.js) with JWT strategy
- Roles stored in JWT: 'user' | 'librarian'
- Middleware protects routes in src/middleware.ts

### Validation
- Zod on every API input — return 422 with field errors on failure

### Tests
- Unit + integration: Jest + ts-jest
- E2E: Playwright
- AI modules: Jest with mocked responses (fixture JSON files)
- Scripts in package.json:
  - test:models, test:api, test:e2e, test:ai, test:auth, test (all)

### AI Modules (implement whichever the user chooses)
- OCR Cataloging: Claude vision API → auto-fill book metadata from cover photo
- Semantic Search: embeddings + client-side ranking against MySQL results
- Chat Assistant: Claude with function calling tools that query the DB directly
- Always wrap AI calls in try/catch and return null on failure — never crash the app

