## ESCALATION PROTOCOL

Escalate to the user ONLY when:
- A required secret/credential is missing and cannot be mocked
- The same test has failed 5+ attempts with genuinely different approaches
- An architectural decision has two paths with major trade-off implications

When escalating, always provide:
1. The exact error message
2. The 3+ approaches already tried
3. A specific A/B question — never an open-ended "what should I do?"

